ce:section.ce:para:
First of all, we have synthesized CDs from the aqueous root extract of red Korean ginseng via microwave irradiation, then RUT was loaded onto the surfaces of CDs via non covalent π- π* interactions and investigated their antioxidant and antibacterial effects (Scheme 1 ). TEM technique was used to determine the shape and size of the as synthesized CDs as displayed in Fig. 1
a & b. TEM study revealed that the CDs were spherical in shape with an average size distribution between 1 and 4 nm and lattice spacing of 0.337 nm (Fig. 1 b & c),. The size was further increased to 60–70 nm following drug loading ( Fig. S1
). EDX analysis showed the presence of carbon and oxygen in the CDs (Fig. 1 d), thereby indicating the presence of several O-containing functional groups. An XRD spectrum of the CDs has been shown in the Fig. 1 e indicating their amorphous nature. Fig. 1 f displayed the Raman spectra in which G and D bands were centred at around 1400 cm−1 and 1589 cm−1 respectively. The average hydrodynamic size of the synthesized CDs was found to be 13.94 ± 1.13 nm and the size was further increased to 175.46 ± 9.20 nm upon drug loading (Fig. 2
a). The Zeta potential values of CDs, RUT, CDs-RUT were −1.67 mV, −0.543 mV and −10.34 mV respectively (
Fig. S2
). The FTIR spectral data (Fig. 2 b) depicted that the ginseng derived CDs showed the major peaks/bands at 3323 cm−1, 2925 cm−1, 1596–1700 cm−1 and 1017 cm−1 which corresponds to the O-H stretching, C-H stretching, C = O or aromatic C = C stretching and C-O stretching respectively [54]. RUT showed several characteristic peaks of O-H stretching, N-H stretching, C = O stretching, aromatic C = C stretching, and C-O stretching. The transmittance peaks of RUT loaded CDs were identical to those of pure RUT in the range of 500 to 1700 cm−1, indicating the successful loading of RUT onto CDs. Fig. 2 c displayed the photographs of the freshly prepared aqueous solutions of CDs, RUT and CDs-RUT, and indicated that loading of RUT over CDs increased its aqueous solubility (no turbidity was appeared).
